24/10/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- NATO General Secretary Lord George Robertson and Greek Prime Minister Costas Simitis discussed the EU defence policy and NATO's new administrative structure during their meeting in Athens on Thursday (23 October).
Foreign Minister George Papandreou and Defence Minister Yannos Papantoniou also attended the meeting.
The officials declined a NATO request to contribute Greek Army helicopters to the NATO-led peacekeeping force in Afghanistan, citing the huge expenses associated with the 2004 Summer Olympics.
(ANA - 23/10/03)
